                <note rend="inline" type="source">561.311D1/22</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Canadian Chargé</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wrong</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-30">April 30,
                            1931</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I am in receipt of your note Number 66 of April
                    27, 1931 expressing the desire and hope of the Canadian Government that the
                    Government of the United States may see its way clear to participate in the
                    Conference of Wheat Exporting Nations which will assemble on May 19, 1931, in
                    London at Canada House under the chairmanship of the High Commissioner for
                    Canada in Great Britain.</p>
                <pb facs="0751" n="637" xml:id="pg_637"/>
                <p>In reply I have to inform you that this Government accepts the invitation of the
                    Canadian Government and that representatives of the United States will be
                    designated in the near future to attend the Conference.</p>
                <p>I have requested the American Ambassador in London to bring the foregoing
                    informally to the attention of the High Commissioner for Canada in London.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. R. Castle, Jr.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
